    "html":  "\u003cdiv style=\"display:flex; align-items:flex-start; justify-content:space-between; flex-wrap:wrap; gap:12px; margin-bottom:24px;\"\u003e\n  \u003cdiv\u003e\n    \u003cdiv style=\"font-size:11px; font-weight:600; color:#60a5fa; text-transform:uppercase; letter-spacing:0.8px; margin-bottom:6px;\"\u003eDaily Economic Briefing\u003c/div\u003e\n    \u003ch2 style=\"margin:0; font-size:20px; font-weight:700; color:#e2e8f0;\"\u003eTuesday, 07 July 2026\u003c/h2\u003e\n  \u003c/div\u003e\n  \u003cdiv style=\"display:flex; gap:8px; flex-wrap:wrap;\"\u003e\n    \u003cspan style=\"background:rgba(52,211,153,0.12); border:1px solid rgba(52,211,153,0.25); color:#34d399; padding:4px 12px; border-radius:6px; font-size:11px; font-weight:600;\"\u003eMOVE 65.76 Compressed\u003c/span\u003e\n    \u003cspan style=\"background:rgba(52,211,153,0.12); border:1px solid rgba(52,211,153,0.25); color:#34d399; padding:4px 12px; border-radius:6px; font-size:11px; font-weight:600;\"\u003eSOFR 3.63% Stable\u003c/span\u003e\n    \u003cspan style=\"background:rgba(96,165,250,0.12); border:1px solid rgba(96,165,250,0.25); color:#60a5fa; padding:4px 12px; border-radius:6px; font-size:11px; font-weight:600;\"\u003eNFCI \u0026#8722;0.50 Loose\u003c/span\u003e\n    \u003cspan style=\"background:rgba(248,113,113,0.12); border:1px solid rgba(248,113,113,0.25); color:#f87171; padding:4px 12px; border-radius:6px; font-size:11px; font-weight:600;\"\u003eTrade 08:30 ET\u003c/span\u003e\n  \u003c/div\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\n\n\u003cdiv style=\"background:#1a1f2e; border:1px solid #2d3748; border-radius:12px; padding:20px; margin-bottom:20px;\"\u003e\n  \u003cdiv style=\"font-size:11px; font-weight:600; color:#94a3b8; text-transform:uppercase; letter-spacing:0.6px; margin-bottom:14px;\"\u003e\u0026#128202; Liquidity \u0026amp; Stress Metrics \u0026#8212; The \u0026quot;Gnosis\u0026quot; Pulse\u003c/div\u003e\n  \u003cdiv style=\"font-size:12px; color:#64748b; line-height:1.6; margin-bottom:14px;\"\u003eCurrent regime: Structural Expansion with a mild post-holiday normalization in funding. Bond volatility remains compressed, SOFR is stable after the holiday publication gap, and broad financial conditions remain loose.\u003c/div\u003e\n  \u003cdiv style=\"overflow-x:auto;\"\u003e\u003ctable style=\"width:100%; border-collapse:collapse; font-size:13px;\"\u003e\u003cthead\u003e\u003ctr style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #2d3748;\"\u003e\u003cth style=\"text-align:left; padding:8px 12px; color:#64748b; font-weight:600; text-transform:uppercase; font-size:10px; letter-spacing:0.5px;\"\u003eMetric\u003c/th\u003e\u003cth style=\"text-align:right; padding:8px 12px; color:#64748b; font-weight:600; text-transform:uppercase; font-size:10px; letter-spacing:0.5px;\"\u003eValue\u003c/th\u003e\u003cth style=\"text-align:left; padding:8px 12px; color:#64748b; font-weight:600; text-transform:uppercase; font-size:10px; letter-spacing:0.5px;\"\u003eMarket Context\u003c/th\u003e\u003cth style=\"text-align:center; padding:8px 12px; color:#64748b; font-weight:600; text-transform:uppercase; font-size:10px; letter-spacing:0.5px;\"\u003eStatus\u003c/th\u003e\u003c/tr\u003e\u003c/thead\u003e\u003ctbody\u003e\u003ctr style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #1e293b;\"\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:10px 12px; color:#e2e8f0; font-weight:500;\"\u003eMOVE Index\u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:10px 12px; text-align:right; color:#34d399; font-weight:700;\"\u003e65.76\u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:10px 12px; color:#94a3b8; text-align:left;\"\u003eTreasury volatility remains in a low/compressed band. That keeps term-premium shock risk contained unless today\u0026apos;s trade deficit or auction demand jolts the curve.\u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:10px 12px; text-align:center;\"\u003e\u003cspan style=\"background:rgba(52,211,153,0.12); border:1px solid rgba(52,211,153,0.25); color:#34d399; padding:3px 10px; border-radius:6px; font-size:11px; font-weight:600;\"\u003eCompressed\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\u003c/tr\u003e\u003ctr style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #1e293b;\"\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:10px 12px; color:#e2e8f0; font-weight:500;\"\u003eSOFR Rate\u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:10px 12px; text-align:right; color:#34d399; font-weight:700;\"\u003e3.63%\u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:10px 12px; color:#94a3b8; text-align:left;\"\u003eLatest New York Fed/FRED print shows secured overnight funding stable after quarter-end and holiday effects eased.\u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:10px 12px; text-align:center;\"\u003e\u003cspan style=\"background:rgba(52,211,153,0.12); border:1px solid rgba(52,211,153,0.25); color:#34d399; padding:3px 10px; border-radius:6px; font-size:11px; font-weight:600;\"\u003eStable\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\u003c/tr\u003e\u003ctr\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:10px 12px; color:#e2e8f0; font-weight:500;\"\u003eNFCI\u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:10px 12px; text-align:right; color:#60a5fa; font-weight:700;\"\u003e\u0026#8722;0.50\u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:10px 12px; color:#94a3b8; text-align:left;\"\u003eChicago Fed\u0026apos;s latest weekly reading remains negative, meaning financial conditions are looser than average across risk, credit, and leverage channels.\u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:10px 12px; text-align:center;\"\u003e\u003cspan style=\"background:rgba(96,165,250,0.12); border:1px solid rgba(96,165,250,0.25); color:#60a5fa; padding:3px 10px; border-radius:6px; font-size:11px; font-weight:600;\"\u003eLoose\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\u003c/tr\u003e\u003c/tbody\u003e\u003c/table\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\n  \u003cdiv style=\"margin-top:16px; padding:14px 16px; background:rgba(96,165,250,0.06); border-left:3px solid #60a5fa; border-radius:0 8px 8px 0;\"\u003e\n    \u003cdiv style=\"font-size:10px; font-weight:700; color:#60a5fa; text-transform:uppercase; letter-spacing:0.6px; margin-bottom:6px;\"\u003eGnosis Interpretation\u003c/div\u003e\n    \u003cdiv style=\"font-size:13px; color:#94a3b8; line-height:1.6;\"\u003eThe liquidity stack still supports risk: MOVE is compressed, SOFR has normalized after the holiday gap, and NFCI remains loose. The main risk is not plumbing stress; it is whether today\u0026apos;s larger trade-deficit data or the 3-Year auction steepens rate sensitivity enough to interrupt equity momentum.\u003c/div\u003e\n  \u003c/div\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\n\n\u003cdiv style=\"background:#1a1f2e; border:1px solid #2d3748; border-radius:12px; padding:20px; margin-bottom:20px;\"\u003e\n  \u003cdiv style=\"font-size:11px; font-weight:600; color:#94a3b8; text-transform:uppercase; letter-spacing:0.6px; margin-bottom:14px;\"\u003e\u0026#128197; Economic Calendar: 2026-07-07\u003c/div\u003e\n  \u003cdiv style=\"font-size:12px; color:#64748b; line-height:1.6; margin-bottom:14px;\"\u003eBuilt from reliable sources only. Census/BEA released May trade at 08:30 ET; BLS confirms JOLTS is not today and is next scheduled for August 4; TreasuryDirect lists a 3-Year Note auction today. The NY Fed also released June consumer expectations, adding inflation-expectations context.\u003c/div\u003e\n  \u003cdiv style=\"overflow-x:auto;\"\u003e\u003ctable style=\"width:100%; border-collapse:collapse; font-size:13px;\"\u003e\u003cthead\u003e\u003ctr style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #2d3748;\"\u003e\u003cth style=\"text-align:left; padding:8px 12px; color:#64748b; font-weight:600; text-transform:uppercase; font-size:10px; letter-spacing:0.5px;\"\u003eEvent\u003c/th\u003e\u003cth style=\"text-align:center; padding:8px 12px; color:#64748b; font-weight:600; text-transform:uppercase; font-size:10px; letter-spacing:0.5px;\"\u003eEST (US)\u003c/th\u003e\u003cth style=\"text-align:center; padding:8px 12px; color:#64748b; font-weight:600; text-transform:uppercase; font-size:10px; letter-spacing:0.5px;\"\u003eGMT+8 (Local)\u003c/th\u003e\u003cth style=\"text-align:center; padding:8px 12px; color:#64748b; font-weight:600; text-transform:uppercase; font-size:10px; letter-spacing:0.5px;\"\u003eImportance\u003c/th\u003e\u003cth style=\"text-align:left; padding:8px 12px; color:#64748b; font-weight:600; text-transform:uppercase; font-size:10px; letter-spacing:0.5px;\"\u003eNotes\u003c/th\u003e\u003c/tr\u003e\u003c/thead\u003e\u003ctbody\u003e\u003ctr style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #1e293b;\"\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:10px 12px; color:#e2e8f0;\"\u003eUS May International Trade in Goods and Services\u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:10px 12px; color:#94a3b8; text-align:center;\"\u003e08:30\u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:10px 12px; color:#94a3b8; text-align:center;\"\u003e20:30\u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:10px 12px; text-align:center;\"\u003e\u003cspan style=\"color:#f87171; font-weight:600; font-size:12px;\"\u003eHigh\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:10px 12px; color:#64748b; font-size:12px;\"\u003eMay deficit widened to $77.6B as exports fell and imports rose. Watch GDP tracking, dollar sensitivity, and industrial/capital-goods read-through.\u003c/td\u003e\u003c/tr\u003e\u003ctr style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #1e293b;\"\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:10px 12px; color:#e2e8f0;\"\u003eNY Fed Survey of Consumer Expectations\u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:10px 12px; color:#94a3b8; text-align:center;\"\u003eReleased\u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:10px 12px; color:#94a3b8; text-align:center;\"\u003eReleased\u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:10px 12px; text-align:center;\"\u003e\u003cspan style=\"color:#fbbf24; font-weight:600; font-size:12px;\"\u003eMedium\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:10px 12px; color:#64748b; font-size:12px;\"\u003eJune survey showed short- and medium-term inflation expectations increased while gas-price expectations eased. Useful for Fed path and real-rate narrative.\u003c/td\u003e\u003c/tr\u003e\u003ctr style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #1e293b;\"\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:10px 12px; color:#e2e8f0;\"\u003eUS 3-Year Note Auction\u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:10px 12px; color:#94a3b8; text-align:center;\"\u003e13:00\u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:10px 12px; color:#94a3b8; text-align:center;\"\u003e01:00 (+1)\u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:10px 12px; text-align:center;\"\u003e\u003cspan style=\"color:#f87171; font-weight:600; font-size:12px;\"\u003eHigh\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:10px 12px; color:#64748b; font-size:12px;\"\u003eTreasuryDirect lists $58B 3-Year Note auction. Belly/front-end demand is today\u0026apos;s cleanest liquidity and duration-risk checkpoint.\u003c/td\u003e\u003c/tr\u003e\u003ctr\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:10px 12px; color:#e2e8f0;\"\u003eUS 6-Week Bill Auction\u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:10px 12px; color:#94a3b8; text-align:center;\"\u003e11:30\u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:10px 12px; color:#94a3b8; text-align:center;\"\u003e23:30\u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:10px 12px; text-align:center;\"\u003e\u003cspan style=\"color:#fbbf24; font-weight:600; font-size:12px;\"\u003eMedium\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/td\u003e\u003ctd style=\"padding:10px 12px; color:#64748b; font-size:12px;\"\u003eShort-bill clearing check. Stable demand supports the post-quarter-end funding-normalization thesis.\u003c/td\u003e\u003c/tr\u003e\u003c/tbody\u003e\u003c/table\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\n\n\u003cdiv style=\"background:#1a1f2e; border:1px solid #2d3748; border-radius:12px; padding:20px; margin-bottom:20px;\"\u003e\n  \u003cdiv style=\"font-size:11px; font-weight:600; color:#94a3b8; text-transform:uppercase; letter-spacing:0.6px; margin-bottom:14px;\"\u003e\u0026#127963;\u0026#65039; Geopolitical \u0026amp; Fed Watch\u003c/div\u003e\n  \u003cdiv style=\"background:rgba(52,211,153,0.08); border:1px solid rgba(52,211,153,0.25); border-radius:8px; padding:14px 16px; margin-bottom:12px;\"\u003e\u003cdiv style=\"font-size:11px; font-weight:700; color:#34d399; text-transform:uppercase; letter-spacing:0.5px; margin-bottom:10px;\"\u003eTrade Deficit \u0026amp; Dollar Channel\u003c/div\u003e\u003cul style=\"margin:0; padding-left:18px; font-size:13px;\"\u003e\u003cli style=\"margin-bottom:8px; color:#94a3b8; line-height:1.6;\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eMacro Signal:\u003c/strong\u003e The May trade deficit widened sharply to $77.6B. That can pressure GDP tracking, but it also gives desks a concrete real-economy input rather than a speculative headline.\u003c/li\u003e\u003cli style=\"margin-bottom:8px; color:#94a3b8; line-height:1.6;\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eMarket Lens:\u003c/strong\u003e Watch whether the dollar absorbs the data cleanly. A disorderly FX/rates response would be more important than the headline deficit itself.\u003c/li\u003e\u003c/ul\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\n  \u003cdiv style=\"background:rgba(96,165,250,0.08); border:1px solid rgba(96,165,250,0.25); border-radius:8px; padding:14px 16px; margin-bottom:12px;\"\u003e\u003cdiv style=\"font-size:11px; font-weight:700; color:#60a5fa; text-transform:uppercase; letter-spacing:0.5px; margin-bottom:10px;\"\u003eFed Expectations Watch\u003c/div\u003e\u003cul style=\"margin:0; padding-left:18px; font-size:13px;\"\u003e\u003cli style=\"margin-bottom:8px; color:#94a3b8; line-height:1.6;\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eInflation Expectations:\u003c/strong\u003e NY Fed SCE showed short- and medium-term expectations moved higher while gas-price expectations fell. That mix keeps the Fed narrative data-dependent rather than clearly dovish.\u003c/li\u003e\u003cli style=\"margin-bottom:8px; color:#94a3b8; line-height:1.6;\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eAuction Test:\u003c/strong\u003e The 3-Year auction is the day\u0026apos;s practical Fed-path checkpoint. Strong demand supports the low-volatility thesis; a weak tail would matter for ES through rates.\u003c/li\u003e\u003c/ul\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\n\n\u003cdiv style=\"background:#1a1f2e; border:1px solid #2d3748; border-radius:12px; padding:20px; margin-bottom:20px;\"\u003e\n  \u003cdiv style=\"font-size:11px; font-weight:600; color:#94a3b8; text-transform:uppercase; letter-spacing:0.6px; margin-bottom:14px;\"\u003e\u0026#128200; Trading Strategy Note (ES Futures)\u003c/div\u003e\n  \u003cdiv style=\"background:rgba(52,211,153,0.08); border:1px solid rgba(52,211,153,0.25); border-radius:8px; padding:12px 16px; margin-bottom:10px; font-size:13px; color:#94a3b8; line-height:1.6;\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eThe Breakout Blueprint:\u003c/strong\u003e Liquidity conditions remain supportive while MOVE and NFCI stay calm. The default posture remains buy-the-dip unless rates or breadth begin to reject the expansion.\u003c/div\u003e\n  \u003cdiv style=\"background:rgba(96,165,250,0.08); border:1px solid rgba(96,165,250,0.25); border-radius:8px; padding:12px 16px; margin-bottom:10px; font-size:13px; color:#94a3b8; line-height:1.6;\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eTarget Horizons:\u003c/strong\u003e Keep the structural high-call map intact, but separate that from intraday execution. Today\u0026apos;s trade data and 3-Year auction can create short, rates-driven volatility pockets.\u003c/div\u003e\n  \u003cdiv style=\"background:rgba(251,191,36,0.08); border:1px solid rgba(251,191,36,0.25); border-radius:8px; padding:12px 16px; margin-bottom:10px; font-size:13px; color:#94a3b8; line-height:1.6;\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eOrder-Flow Execution:\u003c/strong\u003e Monitor 1.5k MotiveWave volume charts around 08:30 ET trade data, 11:30 ET bill clearing, and 13:00 ET 3-Year auction. Avoid fading all-time-high expansion unless rates confirm; treat VAL flushes as long candidates only after absorption prints.\u003c/div\u003e\n  \u003cdiv style=\"background:rgba(148,163,184,0.08); border:1px solid rgba(148,163,184,0.25); border-radius:8px; padding:12px 16px; margin-bottom:10px; font-size:13px; color:#94a3b8; line-height:1.6;\"\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eThe Session Shape:\u003c/strong\u003e Post-holiday liquidity can be uneven. Favor patient entries at high-volume nodes, keep size disciplined into auction time, and do not chase thin vertical extensions after the first impulse.\u003c/div\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e"
